<paragraph id="IAS36_74" base="SL32296" principles="no"><paranum>74</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 36"/><data name="paranum" value="74"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS36_P0275">The <xref base="SL148458" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0106">recoverable amount<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0319"/></ph></xref> of a <xref base="SL148451" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0096">cash&#x2011;generating unit<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0031"/></ph></xref> is the higher of the cash&#x2011;generating unit&#x2019;s <xref base="SL148456" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0101">fair value<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0118"/></ph></xref> less costs of disposal and its <xref base="SL148465" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0112">value in use<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0382"/></ph></xref>. For the purpose of determining the recoverable amount of a cash&#x2011;generating unit, any reference in <xref id="IAS36_X0275" base="A36-235" href="IAS36_19.dita#IAS36_19">paragraphs 19&#x2013;57</xref> to &#x2018;an asset&#x2019; is read as a reference to &#x2018;a cash&#x2011;generating unit&#x2019;.</p></body></paragraph>